Operatives of the Rapid Response Squad say they have rescued a young man who wanted to jump into the lagoon. In a tweet via @rrslagos767, RRS states that the incident happened on the Third Mainland Bridge on the Lagos Island. The operatives said when he was interviewed, the victim of suspected attempted suicide “sounded incoherent.” “He has been taken to Adekunle Police Station for his family to be contacted,” the tweet added. The rescued man is seen wearing a white T-shirt with the inscription, ‘I love China.’ See the tweet: 